Filip Visnjic 2010 // fvda.co.uk // CreativeApplications.Net

Created at the V&A Decode openFrameworks Workshop in London 28/02/2010

iPhone 3Gs  recommended

Features:
- Control particles and their motion by drawing on the screen.
- Tilt control particles or use automated motion
- Change colours in the settings panel or using one of the included presets in the menu below.
- Download desktop application which you can control using your iPhone and OSC Application.

Download from the AppStore here:
http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/prtcl/id359060528?mt=8

Read about this here:
http://www.creativeapplications.net/iphone/prtcl-iphone-openframeworks/

For feature requests add a task here:
http://nokahuna.com/projects/10961/tasks?category=40934

Thanks to Joel Gethin Lewis, Zach Lieberman, Kyle McDonald, Arturo Castro, Andreas Muller, Eduard Prats Molner, Zach Gage, onedotzero and Victoria and Albert Museum.

Created with openFrameworks.

For information on openFrameworks see http://openframeworks.cc

